Text:
Once upon a time, there was a kind princess in this
land.

One day, she helped a little dragon that had gotten
separated from its herd.

The princess and the dragon became fast friends and
grew up together. However, their peaceful days were
coming to an end.

The dragon fought to protect the princess, and even
while suffering a deep wound, took down 10,000
soldiers.

However, what awaited the dragon when he returned to
the princess was a kingdom already destroyed.
The dragon said to the dying princess,

"Princess, open your eyes. Let us soar into the sky
again."

Just then, a single tear fell from the eye of the
seemingly dead princess.
Like the breaking of a dam, the dragon wept.

The warm tears of the dragon soaked the land and
engulfed the kingdom.

When the princess opened her eyes, mysterious,
life-filled water was boiling up.
But, the dragon was nowhere to be found.

The princess called the dragon's name. Her voice
simply echoed into the empty sky.

Maybe what Master Shadow is after is hidden in that
story.
It's the water that intrigues me.
But, even when researching it, it's just a hot spring.
If I use magic, I'll get found out!
Maybe we can't do it alone...

The moment Skel lifts up Po, a device in the wall
activates.
Nothing is impossible for Shadow wisdom.
Then, the entire building begins to shake.
Could it be the tears and hot spring water reacting?
The spring water here does come from underground.
There's no increase in the reaction.
They are Master Shadow's friends after all.

I don't know about under the ground, but in the
legend, the tear came from the princess.
Beta hears a noise behind her and turns around.

A rope wraps around Beta from behind and lifts her
up.
Stop the jokes and help me!
Eta is holding something in her right hand.

It's an artifact that you insert into your buttocks
to help you move your bowels.

Ah, I've been wanting to—wait, where did you get
that?!

As a side-effect, fluid will leak from every orifice
in your body.

That's why I have no problem altering this big-boobed
bimbo until she's a raggedy doll.
Even Master Shadow said, "I hate girls who play dumb."
He said he's fed up with phony silver-haired elves...

Uwaaah! You're lying! You're just trying to make me
cry!

You were selected for this mission, yet you've been
totally useless.
Hm? Is this really Shadow wisdom?

Anyway, it's a training method where you get new
recruits to move by bombarding them with insults.
Hmm... I think she's doing it because she wants to.
—I guess it won't be long before you're tossed aside.
Why...why are you saying such horrible things?!
Tears fall from Beta's eyes and into the hot spring.
Instantly, the building shakes wildly with a rumble.
Ow! Ow! Ow! I give up!

Alpha and the others head to the water park to check
on the situation.
A dragon made of water appears before them.
Is this what Shadow wanted to show us?

Lady Alpha, at this rate the resort will sustain
heavy damage!
We can't let people know we're the Shadow Garden.
I'm doing the best I caaan!!!
Time to say goodbye, ancient weeping dragon.

As soon as Alpha deals the final blow to the dragon,
an overwhelming light fills the area.
After a while, the light subsides...
Golden tears pouring down from the sky...
This must be what Master Shadow was after!

No doubt about it. The hot spring is endowed with
magical power.

It supports beauty and health and relieves high blood
pressure and constipation.
Are there any breast enhancement effects?!
*sob* I'm doing my best. It's hard to be the best.

The dragon draws near Beta's face and licks up her
tears.
It circles around Beta before soaring into the sky.

Shadow must have wanted us to free the soul of that
kindly dragon.
Alright, let's finish things up here!
